01:03.864 --> 01:07.534
So... ocean view,
gulls flying by?

01:07.568 --> 01:09.502
Think this is something
you could get used to?

01:09.537 --> 01:11.938
Well, I-I think I'm more of a
toes-in-the-sand kind of girl.

01:11.973 --> 01:14.040
I like the idea
of waking up in the morning

01:14.075 --> 01:16.543
and rolling out
onto the beach.

01:16.577 --> 01:18.461
Okay, well, then maybe
we can find

01:18.512 --> 01:20.347
a nice little place
on the sand someday

01:20.381 --> 01:21.548
if we, you know...

01:21.582 --> 01:22.599
Survive this?

01:22.633 --> 01:26.102
Yeah.

01:26.137 --> 01:27.120
Hi.

01:27.154 --> 01:28.638
How you doing today?

01:28.689 --> 01:31.758
No shooting.

01:31.776 --> 01:35.094
I don't want the blood
and the mess on the pool deck.

01:37.265 --> 01:38.498
Make them jump.

01:41.619 --> 01:43.153
Think we can survive this?

01:43.204 --> 01:44.571
I don't think so, honey.

01:44.605 --> 01:46.406
Honey?

01:46.440 --> 01:48.808
You talk
like an old married couple.

01:50.011 --> 01:51.962
Well, actually...

01:51.996 --> 01:53.647
No, no, I'm sorry,

01:53.681 --> 01:55.849
I don't care.

01:55.883 --> 01:57.417
Throw them
off the cliff.

01:57.451 --> 01:58.852
Do it and die, Jean Claude.

01:58.886 --> 02:00.553
We just came
for the vase.

02:00.588 --> 02:01.921
It belongs to
our client.

02:01.956 --> 02:04.991
You let us have it
and maybe we'll let you live.

02:05.026 --> 02:06.293
You've fallen
into our trap.

02:06.327 --> 02:07.927
You see, we work
with a master spy,

02:07.962 --> 02:10.864
somebody
who you can't see coming.

02:10.898 --> 02:12.432
In fact, right now,
he's probably...

02:23.744 --> 02:25.945
I want it noted that I took out
six of their guys.

02:27.031 --> 02:29.449
He was taking this.

02:29.483 --> 02:31.668
You thieves have
expensive tastes.

02:31.702 --> 02:33.370
This vase is worth

02:33.421 --> 02:34.888
$6 million.

02:34.922 --> 02:37.757
It's times like these, I wish
I still had the Intersect.

02:37.792 --> 02:39.693
Well, you don't.

02:39.727 --> 02:41.161
What now, Moriarty?

02:41.195 --> 02:42.796
Kill them.

02:42.830 --> 02:44.681
Wait, wait, wait, wait,
wait, wait wait!

02:44.715 --> 02:47.050
We have another master spy.

02:55.526 --> 02:59.178
Okay, yes, yes,
first mission as the Intersect.

02:59.196 --> 03:00.647
You can do this.

03:00.681 --> 03:04.351
They need you, Morgan, so get in
there, okay, and you be a man.

03:04.385 --> 03:07.687
No, be more than a man.

03:07.722 --> 03:09.739
Start with the man part,
just be a man first.

03:09.790 --> 03:12.024
♪ ♪

03:12.043 --> 03:15.028
Keep going, thief, this is fun.

03:15.062 --> 03:16.363
Well, the fun's about to end,
Jean Claude,

03:16.397 --> 03:18.398
because while we've been
standing around chatting,

03:18.432 --> 03:20.700
our other master spy
has been effortlessly breaching

03:20.735 --> 03:22.035
your compound's security.

03:22.069 --> 03:23.202
♪ ♪

03:26.557 --> 03:28.207
I'm good, I'm good.

03:28.225 --> 03:30.677
He's heartless, cruel...

03:30.711 --> 03:34.213
I'm so sorry, fishies,
about your pond.

03:34.231 --> 03:35.949
Whoa, whoa, whoa.

03:35.983 --> 03:37.183
<i>You think your security men</i>

03:37.217 --> 03:39.385
are the best, top-notch?

03:39.403 --> 03:41.521
I admit I do.

03:41.555 --> 03:44.057
<i>Well, our spy</i>
<i>is currently slicing</i>

03:44.091 --> 03:45.959
<i>through them like a hot knife</i>

03:45.993 --> 03:47.243
through butter.

03:50.230 --> 03:52.365
Go on, say something
about you-know-who.

03:52.400 --> 03:54.134
Do I have to?

03:54.168 --> 03:55.535
Yes.

03:55.569 --> 04:00.290
He'll tear your limbs off
and beat you with them.

04:01.675 --> 04:03.977
Okay, okay.

04:04.011 --> 04:08.080
Points for trying,
but where is this master spy?

04:09.082 --> 04:11.050
You looking for me?

04:11.852 --> 04:13.386
Right here, tough guy.

04:14.688 --> 04:17.255
Okay, here we go.

04:17.274 --> 04:18.491
Here we go.

04:18.526 --> 04:21.961
Kill him, too.
Kill them all.

04:21.995 --> 04:24.314
Come on.
Now's the time, buddy.

04:24.365 --> 04:26.566
I'm working on it,
working on it.

04:26.600 --> 04:28.067
And...

04:28.101 --> 04:29.335
we're dead.

04:34.842 --> 04:36.409
Let's dance.

04:37.978 --> 04:40.330
♪ ♪

05:03.988 --> 05:06.339
Who the hell are you?

05:06.373 --> 05:08.741
Charles Carmichael
of Carmichael Industries,

05:08.776 --> 05:11.110
private contractors,
spies for hire.

05:11.145 --> 05:12.111
Don't forget it.

05:15.983 --> 05:19.169
Wow, I really thought
that the latch

05:19.203 --> 05:21.888
was latched,
but, uh...

05:21.922 --> 05:23.339
Buff that right out.
I think we can,

05:23.374 --> 05:27.544
we can still make that--
we'll make that work.

05:27.595 --> 05:29.863
We're still working out
the kinks.

