06:15.463 --> 06:17.111
All righty, folks,

06:17.112 --> 06:18.496
it wasn't a total
catastrophe.

06:18.530 --> 06:20.648
The client was not
interested in the vase

06:20.699 --> 06:25.236
but the microchip inside it,
and that is intact.

06:25.270 --> 06:26.404
Boom.

06:26.438 --> 06:27.405
Señor.

06:27.439 --> 06:28.506
Bang,

06:28.540 --> 06:29.741
we are in the pink.

06:29.775 --> 06:31.993
The vase was going
to be our payment.

06:32.044 --> 06:33.127
And...

06:33.162 --> 06:34.979
still is, fully restored.

06:35.013 --> 06:39.951
Who's not going to pay six mil
for a slightly used Ming vase?

06:43.155 --> 06:46.007
Chuck, we mowed through
the Volkoff fortune

06:46.058 --> 06:47.475
on start-up costs.
I mean,

06:47.509 --> 06:48.760
look at these numbers.

06:48.794 --> 06:51.129
$42 million, which is
still a lot of dough.

06:51.163 --> 06:53.464
Rockets, bullets,
the private jet,

06:53.482 --> 06:55.666
servicing the private
jet, the fresh shrimp

06:55.701 --> 06:58.836
that Morgan likes to eat
on the private jet.

06:58.871 --> 07:01.005
You have to understand they're
just not the same frozen.

07:01.039 --> 07:03.825
They're expensive, and
if we're going to stay solvent,

07:03.859 --> 07:05.476
then we need to collect soon.

07:05.511 --> 07:07.779
Or crawl back to Beckman,
get a government contract.

07:07.813 --> 07:09.614
Never had a problem
with Uncle Sam.

07:09.648 --> 07:11.816
Beat the yahoos
we got coming in here.

07:11.850 --> 07:13.084
Casey, our problem
is not with Uncle Sam,

07:13.118 --> 07:14.252
it's with Clyde Decker,

07:14.286 --> 07:16.154
and I don't see that
changing anytime soon.

07:16.188 --> 07:17.538
Beg, plead.

07:17.589 --> 07:19.290
You know I get antsy
taking cases

07:19.324 --> 07:20.691
with moral ambiguity.

07:20.726 --> 07:22.510
Guys, come on.

07:22.544 --> 07:23.895
Sarah,
isn't this

07:23.929 --> 07:24.879
what we wanted?

07:24.930 --> 07:26.497
Come on, Carmichael Industries--

07:26.515 --> 07:29.333
the independence and freedom
to do what we want when we want,

07:29.368 --> 07:30.835
and we're doing good,
we're doing good.

07:30.869 --> 07:32.236
We got a
solid team.

07:32.271 --> 07:35.573
We just need a little more time
to get our feet on solid ground.

07:35.607 --> 07:37.525
And, in the meantime,
we work for dirtbags.

07:39.178 --> 07:41.145
Chuck, you're handling this
really well.

07:41.180 --> 07:42.363
I mean, all the
bumps in the road

07:42.397 --> 07:43.681
and Morgan

07:43.699 --> 07:46.200
with the Intersect
and you without it.

07:46.235 --> 07:48.035
Which is fine.

07:48.070 --> 07:49.921
Morgan, yes, has
the Intersect now,

07:49.955 --> 07:51.923
but I'm, I'm
happy for him.

07:51.957 --> 07:55.760
Plus, I get to work
with my smokin' hot wife

07:55.794 --> 07:57.228
and my best friends.

07:57.262 --> 07:58.763
Who could ask for
anything more?

07:58.797 --> 08:00.798
Okay.

08:02.367 --> 08:03.868
What was that?

08:03.902 --> 08:04.902
What was what?

08:04.937 --> 08:07.004
Are you hiding something?

08:07.039 --> 08:08.606
Why would I need
to hide anything?

08:08.640 --> 08:10.758
Okay.

08:10.809 --> 08:12.543
Okay.

08:12.578 --> 08:13.544
<i>Morgan, Operation</i>

08:13.579 --> 08:15.479
VFTB is dead.

08:15.514 --> 08:16.881
"View from the
Bluff" is dead?

08:16.899 --> 08:19.417
Chuck, I found the
perfect house for you guys.

08:19.451 --> 08:20.751
Well, except
that I was wrong

08:20.786 --> 08:22.236
and Sarah doesn't want
a house on the bluff.

08:22.271 --> 08:23.588
She wants her toes
in the sand.

08:23.622 --> 08:25.489
Okay, fine, "Operation
Toes in the Sand."

08:25.524 --> 08:28.426
Actually, it makes
a better acronym.

08:28.460 --> 08:30.244
Toes in the Sa--
T.I.T...

08:30.279 --> 08:31.696
Why don't, why don't,
why don't we

08:31.730 --> 08:32.929
just call it
"Operation Toes," okay?

08:32.965 --> 08:35.783
Oh, fine, fine, I'll
start my research.

08:35.833 --> 08:38.703
Oh, Chuck, I know you've
been setting aside funds

08:38.736 --> 08:41.304
for this house, you know,
and I hope my accident

08:41.340 --> 08:43.474
with the vase didn't,
didn't blow it for you.

08:43.508 --> 08:45.626
No, hey, hey,
don't worry about it.

08:45.677 --> 08:48.312
We've got a very promising
potential client.

08:48.347 --> 08:49.380
We're going to wine
and dine him

08:49.414 --> 08:51.582
and, soon enough,
we will be raking it in.

08:51.617 --> 08:52.950
Good, and you know what?

08:52.985 --> 08:55.219
If it all goes south,
well, we still have...

08:55.254 --> 08:56.587
The Buy More.

08:56.622 --> 08:59.473
She's served us well
over the years.

08:59.524 --> 09:03.093
It all seems so normal,

09:03.111 --> 09:04.996
a little too normal.

09:05.030 --> 09:06.731
Yeah.

09:06.765 --> 09:09.533
Sleeping dogs, though;
sleeping dogs.

09:10.619 --> 09:11.569
Oh, it's Casey.

09:11.603 --> 09:12.803
Wants us down in Castle.

09:12.838 --> 09:14.822
Yeah, all right.

09:20.946 --> 09:22.446
Hoist the flag.

09:29.121 --> 09:30.187
Hey, Casey,

09:30.222 --> 09:31.339
what do you need?

09:31.390 --> 09:32.356
The client's here.

09:32.391 --> 09:33.341
I don't like him.

09:33.392 --> 09:34.892
What?
The who, the what?

09:34.927 --> 09:36.260
The client--
the client is here?

09:36.294 --> 09:37.662
- Hmm.
- I thought we were going to wine

09:37.696 --> 09:38.796
and dine the guy,
charm him.

09:38.830 --> 09:40.331
Waste of time--
he's here now.

09:40.365 --> 09:42.683
Casey, this is supposed
to be a secret base.

09:42.734 --> 09:44.936
I took precautions.

09:44.970 --> 09:46.971
Oh, good.

09:50.158 --> 09:52.276
Casey, what precautions?

09:57.482 --> 10:00.217
What the hell kind
of operation is this?

10:00.252 --> 10:03.454
We're still working out
the kinks.

10:03.488 --> 10:05.456
<i>$20 million</i>

10:05.490 --> 10:08.526
was stolen from me
by a high-level Ponzi schemer.

10:08.560 --> 10:10.027
You heard the name
Roger Bale?

10:10.062 --> 10:11.462
Well, you will soon.

10:11.496 --> 10:13.297
He's bilked investors
to the tune

10:13.332 --> 10:14.966
of about a half
a billion dollars.

10:15.000 --> 10:16.167
Why not go
to the cops?

10:16.201 --> 10:17.168
I did,

10:17.202 --> 10:18.903
but Bale has falsified records,

10:18.937 --> 10:20.187
saying he lost the
money in normal trading

10:20.222 --> 10:21.706
and he's broke,

10:21.740 --> 10:23.040
but he keeps buying
property in St. Martin.

10:23.075 --> 10:24.809
He's a thief.

10:24.843 --> 10:26.344
The heart
of Bale's operation

10:26.378 --> 10:29.413
is a computer vault
in his corporate headquarters.

10:29.448 --> 10:32.249
Access the accounts,
get my money.

10:32.284 --> 10:33.851
Yes, we ride
at midnight.

10:33.885 --> 10:35.202
His security is deadly.

10:36.621 --> 10:38.823
So maybe, maybe we, we ride
first thing in the morning.

10:38.857 --> 10:40.024
- No need to rush.
- That's probably a better idea.

10:40.042 --> 10:41.859
Twenty percent

10:41.893 --> 10:44.762
of what you recover is yours.

10:47.432 --> 10:48.933
Fifty.

10:50.369 --> 10:51.669
Done some digging
on you, Woodley.

10:51.703 --> 10:54.105
You're just an ambulance
chaser, trial lawyer,

10:54.139 --> 10:55.106
scum of the earth.

10:55.140 --> 10:56.774
Uh! He's kidding.

10:56.808 --> 10:58.509
He's kidding.
He's only kidding.

10:58.543 --> 11:00.878
Casey, Bale is worth
infiltrating anyway.

11:00.912 --> 11:02.747
Looks like he's stolen money
from teachers' unions

11:02.781 --> 11:04.915
and families.

11:04.950 --> 11:07.518
He stole $2 million
from Rush Limbaugh.

11:07.552 --> 11:11.522
Tell me everything you know
about this animal.

11:14.126 --> 11:16.577
<i>He's throwing himself a party</i>
<i>tomorrow night--</i>

11:16.611 --> 11:19.063
<i>his going-away--</i>
<i>but it's strictly invite,</i>

11:19.097 --> 11:21.899
<i>and everything goes</i>
<i>through his secure Blackberry.</i>

11:21.933 --> 11:23.701
What a complete tool.

11:23.735 --> 11:25.753
Blah-blah-blah-blah-blah
on the Bluetooth,

11:25.787 --> 11:26.837
all day-- how rude.

11:26.872 --> 11:27.938
I'm getting

11:27.973 --> 11:29.256
a really good feed
from the satellite.

11:29.291 --> 11:30.941
The party's being set up,
and the place

11:30.976 --> 11:32.009
looks like a fortress.

11:32.044 --> 11:33.210
See? I told you satellite

11:33.245 --> 11:34.211
was a good investment.

11:34.246 --> 11:35.312
We just got to figure out

11:35.347 --> 11:36.547
a way to get into his PDA

11:36.581 --> 11:39.083
and invite ourselves
to this party.

11:39.101 --> 11:41.135
Let's talk
house, homeboy.

11:41.186 --> 11:42.136
What was that?

11:42.187 --> 11:43.137
Did you say house?

11:43.188 --> 11:44.254
Nothing, n-nothing, Sarah.

11:44.272 --> 11:45.556
Just hopping off real quick.

11:48.427 --> 11:49.994
The house is secret, remember?

11:50.028 --> 11:52.563
The only secret,
the only real secret

11:52.597 --> 11:54.231
is gonna be which room
you're sleeping in.

11:54.265 --> 11:56.433
Why? 17 of 'em!

11:56.451 --> 11:59.303
Swimming pool, screening room,
bowling alley, gourmet kitchen,

11:59.337 --> 12:01.122
second... bowling alley,

12:01.156 --> 12:02.773
and it's on the beach.

12:02.808 --> 12:05.076
I mean, it's crazy, but...

12:05.110 --> 12:06.744
Hey, toes in the sand.

12:06.778 --> 12:08.045
Toes in the sand.
Toes in...

12:08.080 --> 12:09.380
Toes in the sand!

12:09.414 --> 12:12.299
Could you imagine how awesome
this would be, buddy?

12:12.334 --> 12:14.668
I mean, to give Sarah
the dream life?

12:14.719 --> 12:16.587
Owning her own company,
living in the dream home,

12:16.621 --> 12:18.305
a place that we
can call our own.

12:18.340 --> 12:20.624
We just need
this gig to pay out.

12:20.659 --> 12:22.960
I know.

12:22.978 --> 12:24.345
One second.

12:32.170 --> 12:34.171
Chuck, why don't we just nab

12:34.206 --> 12:35.673
this guy's phone
while he's playing squash?

12:35.707 --> 12:37.992
Huh?
I just zoomed on his gym bag.

12:38.026 --> 12:39.326
Okay? Kensington Athletic.

12:39.361 --> 12:40.845
It's, like a super
exclusive squash club.

12:40.879 --> 12:42.163
He's got to have
a regular game, right?

12:42.197 --> 12:43.831
Morgan, that's fantastic.

12:43.865 --> 12:46.150
Fantastic!

12:46.184 --> 12:47.118
Zoomed?

12:47.152 --> 12:48.486
Did you say you... what?

12:48.520 --> 12:50.855
Did you... you said
you zoomed on his gym bag?

12:50.889 --> 12:52.173
Yes, yeah, because
you had "flash,"

12:52.207 --> 12:53.791
which was
great, but...

12:53.825 --> 12:55.292
mmm... I kind of want
to do my own thing,

12:55.326 --> 12:57.027
mix it up a little bit,
so I came up with zoom.

12:58.330 --> 12:59.880
You don't like it.
Ah, you don't like it.

12:59.931 --> 13:00.881
No, hey, hey--

13:00.932 --> 13:02.733
"zoom" it is, buddy. You know.

13:02.767 --> 13:03.968
Whatever you want.

13:04.002 --> 13:05.686
Really?
You're-you're amazing.

13:05.720 --> 13:08.139
You are so Zen right now.
If I had a power like that

13:08.173 --> 13:09.440
and I thought
it was gone forever,

13:09.474 --> 13:10.558
aw, Chuck, I'd be a wreck.

13:10.609 --> 13:13.210
Whew! But not you,
man, you are my hero.

13:13.245 --> 13:15.846
You're great even
without the Intersect.

13:20.018 --> 13:22.820
How certain are you
that these glasses

13:22.854 --> 13:25.322
only had one reload
left in them?

13:25.357 --> 13:28.792
Like...
very certain.

13:28.827 --> 13:30.194
I tried to access

13:30.228 --> 13:33.364
the program, but there
was no way to update it.

13:33.398 --> 13:37.201
This version of the Intersect
is a one-time deal-- I'm sorry.

13:40.088 --> 13:41.772
That's okay.
That's okay.

13:41.806 --> 13:43.040
Morgan's got it now,

13:43.058 --> 13:46.060
and he's doing
surprisingly well, so...

13:47.445 --> 13:49.914
Chuck, what's wrong?

13:50.949 --> 13:53.150
The Intersect

13:53.185 --> 13:55.152
opened me up
to big dreams.

13:55.187 --> 13:57.855
But in order for those
dreams to become a reality,

13:57.889 --> 14:01.592
I need this business
to succeed, and...

14:01.626 --> 14:02.993
You think the company
doesn't work

14:03.028 --> 14:04.361
if you don't have the Intersect?

14:06.264 --> 14:07.565
Yeah.

14:07.599 --> 14:11.252
Chuck, I don't think that Dad
wanted you to have

14:11.286 --> 14:12.753
the Intersect forever.

14:12.787 --> 14:15.606
And besides,
you don't need it.

14:16.775 --> 14:18.776
The computer
didn't make you a hero,

14:18.810 --> 14:21.779
it just gave you
an opportunity to become one.

14:21.813 --> 14:24.281
Now it's up to you.

14:24.316 --> 14:26.183
The training wheels are off,
you're gonna fall down,

14:26.218 --> 14:28.786
but I promise you...
you can do this.

14:31.790 --> 14:33.958
My two cents.

14:35.393 --> 14:37.444
Thanks, sis.

14:37.479 --> 14:40.281
I needed a good
Ellie speech.

14:40.315 --> 14:42.283
Well, what are sisters for?

14:58.088 --> 15:01.140
The mission, is to
access Roger Bale's PDA

15:01.206 --> 15:03.891
and put ourselves on the guest
list for his party tonight.

15:03.892 --> 15:06.260
The phone is gonna be
difficult to get to,

15:06.294 --> 15:08.862
and password-protected
when we do.

15:08.897 --> 15:10.430
Bale has bodyguards;
could be trouble.

15:10.465 --> 15:13.199
And that's why you're the one
going for the phone, Casey.

15:13.218 --> 15:14.334
This plug-in

15:14.369 --> 15:15.836
will cut through
all the encryption

15:15.870 --> 15:18.272
and install a virus that
will send me an invite.

15:18.306 --> 15:20.107
Bale is playing
in a club

15:20.141 --> 15:21.875
squash tournament.
Morgan,

15:21.910 --> 15:23.877
you're gonna delay his
opponent while I step in

15:23.895 --> 15:25.545
and match up with Bale.

15:25.563 --> 15:27.581
He'll get to know my face
and name so that when

15:27.615 --> 15:29.716
I show up at the party,
I won't be a complete stranger.

15:29.734 --> 15:32.753
What? What-what-what,
what's the problem? What's up?

15:32.787 --> 15:35.756
You're gonna play?
Do you actually

15:35.790 --> 15:37.958
play any non-video game sports?

15:37.992 --> 15:39.443
Yeah, I played
some racquetball.

15:39.494 --> 15:42.062
I think I can fake
squash for half an hour.

15:43.097 --> 15:45.265
No, Chuck,
I don't think so.

15:45.300 --> 15:46.967
I... Sarah.

15:48.937 --> 15:50.454
Uh... well,

15:50.488 --> 15:52.906
sweetheart, um...

15:52.941 --> 15:56.043
you know, I-I think what, um...

15:56.077 --> 15:57.210
Let's put Grimes
on the court.

15:57.245 --> 15:59.046
He can zoom on squash,
give the guy a game.

16:00.081 --> 16:01.615
"Zoom," Casey?

16:01.649 --> 16:03.116
It'll buy me some time.

16:03.151 --> 16:04.217
You delay his opponent,

16:04.252 --> 16:05.719
take over the job
I was gonna do.

16:05.753 --> 16:07.921
It'll be great, right?
What was the job I was gonna do?

16:11.592 --> 16:12.793
Yeah...

16:12.827 --> 16:13.927
Oof...

16:13.962 --> 16:15.261
I think I'm
supposed to be

16:15.280 --> 16:17.564
playing my game right now.
You sure it's only 2:00?

16:17.598 --> 16:20.767
Oh, Mr. Burnham,
you just sit here and relax.

16:20.802 --> 16:22.970
I will tell you when it's time.

16:23.004 --> 16:24.621
And right now, it is...

16:24.656 --> 16:25.989
not time.

16:29.744 --> 16:31.328
Bale's coming.

16:31.379 --> 16:33.013
Casey, he's headed your way.

16:33.047 --> 16:36.350
Morgan, get ready,
he'll be there in a minute.

16:36.384 --> 16:37.617
Yep.

16:39.320 --> 16:41.521
Chuck, you keep
that bear on that table,

16:41.556 --> 16:42.723
or this all falls apart.

16:42.757 --> 16:43.924
Remember,

16:43.958 --> 16:46.493
I like it deep... and hard.

16:47.528 --> 16:48.629
That's great.

16:48.663 --> 16:50.330
That just sounds great.

16:55.403 --> 16:57.137
Hey, man, sorry
for the delay.

16:57.155 --> 17:00.190
I had a hot tub
full of nursing students.

17:00.241 --> 17:02.526
- They're so chatty.
- Totally.

17:02.577 --> 17:04.678
So, you must be

17:04.712 --> 17:05.679
Killer Burnham?

17:05.713 --> 17:06.780
He's a no-show.

17:06.814 --> 17:07.814
I'm Michael Carmichael

17:07.848 --> 17:08.815
of Michael Carmichael
Industries,

17:08.833 --> 17:09.849
a subsidiary of MikeCo.

17:09.884 --> 17:11.785
That sounds like big money.

17:11.819 --> 17:13.819
Mmm, you have no idea.

17:13.855 --> 17:16.289
You know, if was standing
on my wallet...

17:16.323 --> 17:17.790
I'd be tall.

17:17.825 --> 17:18.842
Yeah.

17:18.876 --> 17:19.893
Your skin is...

17:19.926 --> 17:21.127
soft to the touch.

17:21.162 --> 17:22.295
There you go.

17:22.329 --> 17:23.829
Is that a
waxing situation?

17:23.865 --> 17:25.632
My wife's talked to me
about waxing, but...

17:25.665 --> 17:27.500
I'm not really a big fan
of physical contact.

17:27.518 --> 17:28.902
Outside of my job, of course.

17:28.936 --> 17:30.837
This is what I do every day.

17:35.526 --> 17:37.911
Hey, uh, your ball warm?

17:39.147 --> 17:40.346
Here we go.

17:46.404 --> 17:48.872
Amigo, my ball is...

17:48.906 --> 17:50.157
red-hot.

17:53.695 --> 17:55.028
You're pretty quick.

17:55.046 --> 17:56.413
"Sneaky quick," they call that.

17:56.464 --> 17:57.998
Ooh! Sneaky quick.

18:04.605 --> 18:05.839
Put a little elbow
grease into it.

18:05.873 --> 18:07.841
Oh, yeah? Should I do that?

18:07.875 --> 18:09.559
There you go.
There it is.

18:09.594 --> 18:10.877
Almost there.

18:10.912 --> 18:13.380
Almost there.

18:13.414 --> 18:14.681
Little deeper.

18:14.716 --> 18:15.882
You know...

18:15.900 --> 18:18.085
you are a thick man.

18:18.119 --> 18:19.786
Yeah... right there.

18:19.821 --> 18:20.954
There it is.

18:20.988 --> 18:22.556
Come on.

18:27.061 --> 18:30.030
Turn and reach,
you old son of a bitch.

18:30.064 --> 18:32.866
Hey, Chuck, we got a problem.

18:32.900 --> 18:33.934
Casey's caught up
getting Bale's phone.

18:33.968 --> 18:35.102
Maybe I can tranq my guy

18:35.136 --> 18:36.236
and give Casey an assist.

18:39.791 --> 18:41.341
- So, let me ask you a question.
- Yes, sir.

18:41.375 --> 18:44.111
This guy you're supposed
to play, Jim Burnham,

18:44.145 --> 18:46.213
you called him something else.

18:46.247 --> 18:47.380
Killer.

18:47.414 --> 18:48.882
Heard he killed
nine men

18:48.916 --> 18:50.083
in the Foreign Legion.

18:50.101 --> 18:51.218
The name stuck.

18:51.252 --> 18:53.753
Mm, only nine, huh?

18:56.324 --> 18:57.324
What the hell?

18:57.358 --> 18:58.859
No, no, somebody's
not relaxing!

18:58.893 --> 19:00.560
Relax, breathe, breathe.

19:00.594 --> 19:01.594
I just dropped
something.

19:01.612 --> 19:02.779
Oil's slippery.

19:06.868 --> 19:08.452
John Casey.

19:08.486 --> 19:10.270
I knew you'd fall
for that old line.

19:10.304 --> 19:11.972
I haven't seen you
since jump school.

19:13.174 --> 19:14.574
Stark.

19:14.608 --> 19:15.976
Been a while.

19:16.010 --> 19:16.793
Breathe.

19:16.828 --> 19:18.328
Is that a gun?

19:18.379 --> 19:20.613
I am gonna rip

19:20.631 --> 19:21.948
your head off!

19:22.984 --> 19:24.151
What's a leatherneck like you

19:24.185 --> 19:25.452
doing in the Kensington Club?

19:25.486 --> 19:26.987
Private security.

19:27.021 --> 19:29.156
Me, too.
For a turd named Bale.

19:29.190 --> 19:31.658
Real scuzzer, but at
least it's a payday.

19:31.692 --> 19:34.127
I don't have to sell
you on selling out.

19:34.162 --> 19:37.030
Guy with your skills, Casey,
you've got to be raking it in.

19:43.504 --> 19:45.272
Ah!

19:46.808 --> 19:50.210
You think one little dart
is gonna drop 400 pounds

19:50.244 --> 19:51.545
of solid meat?

20:02.657 --> 20:03.707
You seem like a...

20:03.758 --> 20:06.793
moderately successful
individual.

20:06.827 --> 20:08.895
♪ ♪

20:12.099 --> 20:13.666
Let's say a fella
had 40 mil

20:13.684 --> 20:15.501
just kind of lying
around doing nothing.

20:15.520 --> 20:17.103
What would you
do with it?

20:17.138 --> 20:18.471
You looking to invest?

20:18.506 --> 20:19.839
I might be.

20:19.857 --> 20:21.308
I might be.

20:33.237 --> 20:36.857
Aah! Aah! No! No! No!

20:40.962 --> 20:42.412
Good game, Carmichael.

20:44.215 --> 20:47.300
Oh, bunny doll, bunny doll,
Bale; Bale, bunny doll.

20:47.335 --> 20:48.701
Hey, uh,

20:48.719 --> 20:51.171
why don't you guys come to
my party tomorrow night?

20:51.205 --> 20:52.172
Tomorrow night?
Bunny doll,

20:52.206 --> 20:53.539
do we have anything,
uh, planned?

20:53.558 --> 20:54.724
No. I don't think so.

20:54.759 --> 20:56.726
Well, how do you feel?
You want to go?

20:56.761 --> 20:58.562
Oh, I'm game.
Mm.

20:58.596 --> 20:59.679
<i>Excellenté.</i>

20:59.713 --> 21:01.014
Good, good,
good, good, good.

21:01.048 --> 21:02.566
It's a date, then, huh?

21:02.600 --> 21:04.367
Tomorrow night.

21:04.418 --> 21:06.870
♪ ♪

21:12.426 --> 21:13.793
Quit goofing around, Chuck.
We gotta go.

21:13.828 --> 21:15.295
What about the mission?

21:15.329 --> 21:16.796
Don't worry,
Morgan saved the day.

21:16.831 --> 21:18.365
Got an invite to the party.

21:18.399 --> 21:21.001
- Huh?
- Thank God for the Intersect, huh?

21:27.577 --> 21:28.663
Hey, buddy.

21:28.870 --> 21:30.471
Nice work on
the mish today.

21:30.505 --> 21:32.139
Yes.
So listen,

21:32.174 --> 21:34.041
we wired a couple million
dollars into Bale's account.

21:34.059 --> 21:36.510
You're all set for the party.
Would you go Bogart

21:36.545 --> 21:38.103
with the white tux,
or would you go Bond

21:38.128 --> 21:39.328
with the black tux?

21:40.398 --> 21:42.616
Uh... black, definitely.

21:42.651 --> 21:44.585
I knew it. I knew black tux.
Always bet on black.

21:44.619 --> 21:46.520
Right?

21:46.555 --> 21:47.605
Okay, what's wrong?

21:47.656 --> 21:50.291
Chuck, is this
Intersect withdrawal?

21:50.325 --> 21:52.259
I mean, are you...
are you missing it?

21:53.995 --> 21:55.562
Sure.

21:55.580 --> 21:58.732
Yeah. Of course,
but it's-it's more than that.

21:58.750 --> 22:00.467
I'm just realizing

22:00.502 --> 22:02.870
how hard it's going
to be without it.

22:02.904 --> 22:04.538
I guess I got used to

22:04.573 --> 22:06.207
our spy missions
being a little bit easier.

22:08.677 --> 22:11.779
But-But remember
the big picture here.

22:11.813 --> 22:13.747
Your beautiful wife,
your perfect home.

22:14.983 --> 22:16.317
It's all right here, buddy.

22:16.351 --> 22:18.118
Toes in the sand.

22:18.153 --> 22:19.386
It's the-the
big picture.

22:19.421 --> 22:20.754
Hey, oh.

22:20.772 --> 22:22.256
I gotta go.

22:22.274 --> 22:23.440
I'll get this to the lab.

22:23.475 --> 22:24.692
Good job, team.
Yeah.

22:24.726 --> 22:25.860
Right, a high
five here.

22:25.894 --> 22:27.027
Good, good, good, good.

22:27.062 --> 22:28.262
Good briefing.

22:28.280 --> 22:30.764
Chuck, do you realize
that I am a trained spy

22:30.782 --> 22:33.000
who can tell when somebody
is keeping a secret?

22:33.034 --> 22:36.537
Especially when that someone
happens to be my husband?

22:36.571 --> 22:38.606
It's who I am.

22:38.640 --> 22:40.975
Husband without a secret.

22:41.009 --> 22:44.345
Casey and I are going to scout
Bale's corporate headquarters,

22:44.379 --> 22:46.013
so we'll talk about this later.

22:46.047 --> 22:48.332
Can't this be
that one-time conversation?

23:03.899 --> 23:05.866
This isn't good.

23:05.901 --> 23:08.202
We finally lost control
of the store, haven't we?

23:10.322 --> 23:11.855
All right, where's Jeff?
No...

23:11.907 --> 23:14.074
Where's Lester?
I can sense his

23:14.109 --> 23:16.243
evil little hand
all over this.

23:19.531 --> 23:20.664
Hey, Jeff.

23:30.759 --> 23:32.927
Heartbreaking, isn't it?

23:32.961 --> 23:34.995
What happened?

23:35.013 --> 23:36.597
What do you mean?

23:36.631 --> 23:40.551
Is this about poor
Jeffrey over there?

23:40.602 --> 23:41.885
Poor Jeffrey?
Poor Jeffrey?

23:41.937 --> 23:43.771
He was trampled by a stampede

23:43.805 --> 23:46.006
of middle-aged secretaries
during the midnight release of

23:46.024 --> 23:48.042
the talking Justin Bieber doll.

23:48.076 --> 23:50.027
His legs were crushed.

23:50.061 --> 23:53.397
He may never walk again.

23:53.448 --> 23:55.716
But you would know that

23:55.750 --> 23:57.517
if you ever bothered to come in

23:57.535 --> 23:59.370
and actually
manage the store, Grimes.

23:59.404 --> 24:01.255
Or you, Bartowski,
if you ever bothered

24:01.289 --> 24:03.624
to come by
and check up on your friends.

24:03.658 --> 24:06.293
Shame!

24:06.328 --> 24:08.379
Shame.

24:11.399 --> 24:15.085
Morgan, I can't believe it.

24:15.136 --> 24:16.870
It's terrible.
I feel so bad!

24:16.905 --> 24:20.040
No, Morgan, I mean,
I literally can't believe it.

24:20.058 --> 24:21.541
Really? This?
They wouldn't. They couldn't.

24:21.559 --> 24:23.710
What am I talking about?
It's Jeff and Lester.

24:23.728 --> 24:25.479
Of course it's a scam.

24:25.513 --> 24:27.581
Of course.

24:31.353 --> 24:33.904
Please help.
Buy More insurance ran out.

24:33.938 --> 24:35.990
The audacity.

24:36.024 --> 24:37.941
As the secret owner
of this establishment,

24:37.993 --> 24:40.110
I happen to know
we have excellent insurance.

24:40.161 --> 24:41.795
Listen, how are
we going to prove that

24:41.830 --> 24:43.397
Jeff and Lester are
bilking it from the store?

24:43.431 --> 24:44.832
Well, maybe we construct

24:44.866 --> 24:47.334
some sort of ruse, you know, and
trick him up out of the chair.

24:47.369 --> 24:49.503
Or we could... Hang on.

24:53.458 --> 24:55.742
Or we could wait for him

24:55.760 --> 24:57.911
to stand up like
the moron that he is.

24:57.929 --> 24:59.346
Yeah.
Mm.

25:00.465 --> 25:02.583
Mr. Barnes, this is some
sort of insurance scam?!

25:02.617 --> 25:04.585
Hey, guys.

25:04.619 --> 25:07.021
Jeff, you're gonna give back
every penny, or you're going

25:07.055 --> 25:08.255
to jail.
To see my mom?

25:08.273 --> 25:09.323
Whoa! Whoa!
Whoa! Whoa! Whoa!

25:09.357 --> 25:11.358
Hey, guys, guys,
what are you doing?

25:11.393 --> 25:13.260
This is a very
sick man here.

25:13.278 --> 25:16.480
Ah! Ah, my gosh!

25:16.531 --> 25:18.982
Jeffrey,
you can walk!

25:19.034 --> 25:20.401
Guys, it's a miracle.

25:20.435 --> 25:21.702
It's a miracle.

25:21.736 --> 25:23.987
This is because
of your donations.

25:32.547 --> 25:33.797
Shame.

25:33.832 --> 25:35.716
Shame.
Shame.

25:39.838 --> 25:43.457
I think we may need to spend
some more time at the Buy More.

25:43.475 --> 25:45.626
Yeah, we do. Oh!

25:45.660 --> 25:48.695
Oh, I forgot-- Sarah
wants to have a talk.

25:48.730 --> 25:50.497
She knows I'm keeping
a secret from her.

25:50.532 --> 25:52.800
Oh, no. Not the house.

25:52.834 --> 25:55.369
- She's gonna try and break me.
- Mm-hmm, mm-hmm.

25:55.403 --> 25:58.038
Okay, I'm gonna
hold on to this, right?

25:58.073 --> 26:00.641
And, uh, you go in there,
and you be strong.

26:00.675 --> 26:02.176
Good luck.

26:02.210 --> 26:05.012
Remember, I'm not there
to save you this time.

26:07.048 --> 26:09.349
Sarah?

26:09.384 --> 26:11.385
In a minute!

26:13.154 --> 26:15.255
Um...

26:15.290 --> 26:19.059
so, honey, here's the thing.

26:19.094 --> 26:21.595
Uh, I'm not trying
to keep anything from you.

26:21.629 --> 26:25.099
You are my wife, and-and
that's a part of the deal.

26:25.133 --> 26:26.433
I'm well aware of that.

26:26.468 --> 26:28.469
I would, however, like
to keep a few things

26:28.503 --> 26:31.438
in a special category of

26:31.473 --> 26:34.224
"you don't need
to know aboutness."

26:34.275 --> 26:35.275
Yeah.

26:39.881 --> 26:42.116
♪ ♪

26:49.908 --> 26:52.993
No, no.

26:53.027 --> 26:54.394
Not today.

26:54.429 --> 26:56.196
This has worked in the past.
Not today.

26:56.214 --> 26:57.664
What is it?

26:57.698 --> 26:59.600
This. This. All that.

26:59.634 --> 27:01.535
What's your secret, Chuck?

27:04.005 --> 27:05.172
My lips are sealed.

27:05.206 --> 27:09.510
Well, let me help you
unseal them.

27:16.234 --> 27:17.251
Hand it over.

27:17.285 --> 27:19.887
He cracked like an egg.

27:20.622 --> 27:21.955
It's an acronym.

27:21.990 --> 27:23.223
You see the little dots there?

27:23.241 --> 27:24.691
Whatever.
If you were to break it up

27:24.725 --> 27:27.094
and sound it out phonetically...

27:31.166 --> 27:34.268
It's very sweet, Chuck,
that you tried to surprise me.

27:34.302 --> 27:36.470
With a dream home.

27:36.504 --> 27:38.305
Yeah.
Like that one

27:38.339 --> 27:40.207
right there,
right on the sand.

27:40.241 --> 27:41.808
The perfect house

27:41.843 --> 27:43.710
for the perfect woman.
What do you think?

27:47.081 --> 27:48.148
It's not right, is it?

27:48.183 --> 27:50.951
You know, I-I could just

27:50.985 --> 27:54.922
keep playing detective
and trying to read your mind...

27:54.956 --> 27:58.592
Well, I haven't, um...

27:58.626 --> 28:01.628
Well, this isn't something
that I've ever told anybody.

28:01.663 --> 28:04.298
Hello. Husband.

28:04.332 --> 28:06.099
It's my official title now.

28:06.134 --> 28:08.168
I have a ring
to prove it.

28:08.203 --> 28:10.504
You tell me things that
you don't tell other people.

28:12.874 --> 28:16.243
Uh, well, when I was a
little girl, my, uh...

28:16.277 --> 28:18.946
my dad's "work" kept us
moving around a lot.

28:18.980 --> 28:23.617
And I always imagined what a
real family would feel like,

28:23.651 --> 28:26.486
you know, what the perfect
home for us all would be,

28:26.521 --> 28:28.055
and, you know,
the dream house.

28:28.089 --> 28:29.356
This is stupid.

28:29.390 --> 28:32.359
No, no, it's not.
Babe, continue.

28:32.393 --> 28:35.345
Well, I always imagined

28:35.396 --> 28:39.182
a little white house with
a red door and, don't laugh,

28:39.234 --> 28:42.936
but it had a picket fence,
just like, you know,

28:42.971 --> 28:46.039
the houses that you see
on TV that people live in.

28:46.074 --> 28:48.208
Hmm.

28:48.243 --> 28:50.110
Mid-century,
very <i>Leave It to Beaver?</i>

28:50.144 --> 28:54.514
Cozy, homey and simple.

28:54.549 --> 28:55.816
And perfect.

28:56.851 --> 28:59.253
Really?

28:59.287 --> 29:02.623
Sarah, I'm going
to find you your dream home,

29:02.657 --> 29:04.658
whatever it takes.

29:04.692 --> 29:06.827
I'll do anything. I promise.

29:11.132 --> 29:12.666
Testing, one, two.

29:12.700 --> 29:14.268
One, two, three.

29:21.643 --> 29:24.695
Looking good, team.

29:24.729 --> 29:26.546
Especially you, Sarah.

29:26.581 --> 29:29.283
Well, let's have
a great mission, huh, team?

29:29.317 --> 29:31.785
While I sit by myself
in the van.

29:33.371 --> 29:35.989
God, I hope this works.

29:41.732 --> 29:44.232
Allright. Let's go over the plan,
one more time.

29:44.233 --> 29:46.200
Casey, you locate
Bale's computer vault.

29:46.235 --> 29:47.735
Morgan and Sarah, you're gonna
create a distraction,

29:47.770 --> 29:49.470
giving Casey enough time
to get into the vault

29:49.488 --> 29:50.638
and tap into the system.

29:50.656 --> 29:51.823
Got it.

29:53.308 --> 29:55.677
Bale, old man,
good to see you.

29:55.711 --> 29:56.711
Nice to see you.

29:56.745 --> 29:57.645
Right? Yeah,
you remember

29:57.663 --> 29:58.880
Sarah?
I do.

29:58.914 --> 30:01.199
This is Chalmers, my mute

30:01.250 --> 30:02.316
manservant.

30:02.351 --> 30:03.651
We have received
your wire

30:03.669 --> 30:05.036
and account
information.

30:05.087 --> 30:08.656
On behalf of our investors,
we're very excited

30:08.691 --> 30:09.824
to have you aboard.

30:09.858 --> 30:10.892
Oh, I bet. I bet.

30:10.926 --> 30:13.127
Follow me.

30:13.162 --> 30:15.163
Will do.

30:16.164 --> 30:18.165
I was to be
your accountant.

30:18.183 --> 30:19.967
What I did was,
I improvised.

30:20.002 --> 30:21.436
Okay.

30:21.470 --> 30:22.887
Morgan, buddy,
you're doing great.

30:22.938 --> 30:24.889
You're doing great.
Just stay on point.

30:24.940 --> 30:27.008
Remember the mission.
Casey, you're up.

30:37.252 --> 30:39.220
Excellent. Excellent,
Casey. Excellent.

30:39.254 --> 30:40.755
Fiber optic cable leads
all the way

30:40.789 --> 30:42.073
down that hall. That's probably
where the vault is.

30:42.124 --> 30:43.658
I'll need a key card.

30:43.692 --> 30:44.659
Sarah?

30:44.693 --> 30:45.693
I'm on it.

30:47.296 --> 30:51.065
As you can see, my fortune
is based on shared wealth.

30:51.100 --> 30:55.103
Finding others who enjoy
the better things in life.

30:55.137 --> 30:56.738
Yeah, that's
very bold, Mr. Bale.

30:56.772 --> 30:58.372
Chuck...

30:58.390 --> 31:01.275
this jerk's starting
to get handsy with my girl.

31:01.310 --> 31:03.010
Ourgirl. Yourgirl.

31:03.044 --> 31:04.262
Calm. Calm, Morgan!

31:04.313 --> 31:06.214
Just calm down.
No. No, no, no, no, no, no.

31:06.248 --> 31:07.415
I think I'm gonna zoom, okay?

31:07.449 --> 31:09.183
I can feel it coming on--
a little kung fu.

31:09.217 --> 31:11.052
I am gonna karate chop
this guy in the face.

31:11.086 --> 31:12.236
No, no, no, no. No, no.

31:12.271 --> 31:14.054
Do not do that.
You're gonna zoom too soon.

31:14.072 --> 31:16.557
Premature zoom? Really? Crap!

31:16.592 --> 31:18.392
Okay, okay, what do I do?

31:18.427 --> 31:20.495
Think about baseball.

31:20.529 --> 31:22.130
Baseball.

31:22.164 --> 31:25.566
Why baseball? I mean, come on.
It is so boring.

31:25.601 --> 31:28.736
I mean, just pitch
the damn ball already!

31:28.771 --> 31:31.272
And enough talk
with the statistics!

31:31.306 --> 31:32.874
Chuck, do you know what
a slugging percentage is?

31:32.908 --> 31:34.475
'Cause I don't know what a
slugging percentage is,

31:34.510 --> 31:35.643
all right? And honestly,

31:35.677 --> 31:37.879
who the hell cares?!

31:39.181 --> 31:41.432
All right, that worked.
Thank you, buddy.

31:41.467 --> 31:42.917
Thank you. I'm good.

31:42.951 --> 31:45.920
Perhaps I can show you
around the gardens outside.

31:45.938 --> 31:49.256
They are modeled after the
pleasure gardens of Italy.

31:49.274 --> 31:52.894
Well, the pleasure
would be all mine.

31:52.928 --> 31:54.929
You're a good girl.

31:58.116 --> 31:59.617
What a slime bag.

31:59.651 --> 32:00.968
- Mm.
- Excellent work,

32:01.003 --> 32:02.270
everybody.

32:02.304 --> 32:03.905
Casey is on his way
to the computer vault.

32:03.939 --> 32:05.506
Morgan, Sarah, distraction time.

32:05.541 --> 32:07.842
All righty, Chuck. Am I up?

32:07.876 --> 32:10.178
Oh, you are up, buddy.
Zoom away.

32:17.669 --> 32:19.170
I like that.

32:20.973 --> 32:23.791
Sarah?

32:34.486 --> 32:36.971
Let me show you
how it's done.

32:37.005 --> 32:39.607
♪ ♪

33:01.763 --> 33:03.698
Nice work, Morgan.

33:18.547 --> 33:19.914
We're in.

33:19.948 --> 33:22.817
Bingo. Now, once all
the accounts are downloaded,

33:22.851 --> 33:26.520
we can reroute them
to the original investors.

33:27.856 --> 33:30.758
No, no, no, no, no, no, no.
What's happening?

33:32.361 --> 33:34.028
Decker.

33:34.062 --> 33:35.429
Hello, Chuck.

33:35.464 --> 33:36.597
What are you doing?

33:36.632 --> 33:38.032
I'm using your computer

33:38.066 --> 33:40.384
to access Bale's accounts
and freeze them.

33:40.419 --> 33:41.869
No. No, no, no, no, no.

33:41.904 --> 33:44.205
You're gonna trigger the alarm.
My people are still inside.

33:44.239 --> 33:45.673
<i>Yo</i> people?

33:45.707 --> 33:47.091
Cute.

33:59.821 --> 34:02.690
Listen, I know you lied to me,
I know I'm not part

34:02.724 --> 34:05.092
of your bigger plan,
whatever the hell that is, okay?

34:05.127 --> 34:07.028
You've won. Now let us go.

34:07.062 --> 34:09.996
Payback's a bitch, Charlie.

34:11.867 --> 34:14.068
No... Guys, guys,
get out of there!

34:14.085 --> 34:15.202
Mr. Carmichael?

34:18.090 --> 34:21.542
Darling, I know what you
did with my key card.

34:21.576 --> 34:23.577
Come with me now,
or I will kill you

34:23.594 --> 34:25.813
in front of all
of my friends.

34:25.847 --> 34:28.849
Uh-uh. I think actually
what's gonna happen is,

34:28.884 --> 34:30.751
I'm gonna open up
a big can of--

34:33.804 --> 34:35.139
Come with us.
What?

34:37.425 --> 34:39.259
Come with me, Colonel.
Oh, I'm sorry.

34:39.277 --> 34:42.730
You used to be
a colonel.

34:42.764 --> 34:45.599
Morgan, Sarah, Casey, please,
tell me what's happening.

34:59.348 --> 35:01.916
I'm locked out of the accounts!
What have you done?

35:01.950 --> 35:04.218
Do anything to us, and
you'll never have access

35:04.252 --> 35:06.420
to those accounts ever again.

35:06.455 --> 35:08.456
You see, we work with somebody.

35:08.490 --> 35:10.358
A master spy

35:10.392 --> 35:12.360
who always
has a plan.

35:12.394 --> 35:13.894
Okay. Okay, this isn't good.

35:13.929 --> 35:15.496
No plan, no plan.

35:15.530 --> 35:17.264
The master spy
does not have a plan.

35:17.299 --> 35:19.266
Uh, I don't want
to hear her voice anymore.

35:19.300 --> 35:21.135
Take 'em all downstairs.
I'll decide what

35:21.153 --> 35:22.353
to do with them later.

35:22.404 --> 35:24.005
I need you

35:24.039 --> 35:25.806
to get somebody from
our computer team

35:25.841 --> 35:26.974
on the phone <i>right now!</i>

35:27.009 --> 35:28.142
Yes, sir.

35:28.176 --> 35:29.443
I think I have a plan.

35:35.584 --> 35:39.020
Computer emergency?

35:46.864 --> 35:47.909
What's wrong with it?

35:47.983 --> 35:50.285
An outside computer
is accessing your system.

35:50.320 --> 35:52.321
You're under attack.

35:52.355 --> 35:53.989
Don't worry.
I cut into the attack,

35:54.023 --> 35:55.340
and your accounts
are still here.

35:55.375 --> 35:57.442
- Is it fixed?
- Yeppers.

35:57.477 --> 35:58.794
Get rid of him.

35:58.828 --> 36:00.379
Huh? Wait, wait,
wait, wait.

36:00.430 --> 36:01.830
What's happening?
I'm just the IT guy.

36:01.864 --> 36:03.865
You saw some things you
weren't supposed to see.

36:03.900 --> 36:06.201
And I don't like your face.
Kill him.

36:06.235 --> 36:07.235
Then the others.

36:07.270 --> 36:08.670
I'd think twice
about that, Bale!

36:10.373 --> 36:14.142
I pull these wires,
your firewall goes down,

36:14.177 --> 36:16.645
and the CIA is inside of you
in seconds.

36:17.847 --> 36:19.314
Your computer.

36:19.349 --> 36:21.683
Inside of your computer
in seconds.

36:21.718 --> 36:22.751
Who are you?

36:22.785 --> 36:25.320
Carmichael.

36:25.355 --> 36:27.322
Charles Carmichael.

36:27.357 --> 36:29.925
I have your brother Michael.

36:29.959 --> 36:33.061
I know, and you're gonna
let him and the others go.

36:33.096 --> 36:35.030
I so much
as sneeze, and,

36:35.064 --> 36:38.900
well, you lose
all your money.

36:38.935 --> 36:41.086
Oh!

36:41.137 --> 36:44.072
Oops. That was about ten million
bucks right there, Rog.

36:45.842 --> 36:47.409
Let 'em go.

36:50.179 --> 36:52.647
What the hell is going on?

36:52.682 --> 36:55.417
You're free to go.

36:55.451 --> 36:58.620
Hey, Chuck? Chuck,
can you hear me? Where are you?

36:58.654 --> 37:00.489
- Sarah, you outside?
- Yeah.

37:00.523 --> 37:02.107
They let us go.
Are you still inside?

37:03.159 --> 37:05.227
Don't worry about me. Just go.

37:05.261 --> 37:07.079
No, I'm-I'm not going anywhere.

37:07.113 --> 37:08.246
Sarah, you, Casey and Morgan,

37:08.281 --> 37:10.065
get in the van
and leave right now.

37:10.099 --> 37:11.233
Did I do great?

37:11.267 --> 37:12.417
Shut up, moron.

37:12.452 --> 37:14.970
Chuck, I am not leaving
my husband on a mission.

37:15.004 --> 37:17.739
Sarah... Sarah, I'm sorry.

37:19.008 --> 37:20.976
I wanted to buy you the house.

37:21.010 --> 37:23.578
I wanted to give you the future
that you've always dreamed of.

37:23.613 --> 37:25.931
But more than that,
I want you to live.

37:25.965 --> 37:27.182
Come on.
What?

37:27.216 --> 37:28.417
Don't make me die in vain.

37:28.451 --> 37:30.018
Leave me behind.

37:30.052 --> 37:31.686
Get in the van.

37:31.721 --> 37:33.522
Leave. Leave me behind!

37:35.224 --> 37:37.091
Casey, we can't just
leave him behind like that.

37:37.110 --> 37:38.160
Please, leave!

37:40.730 --> 37:44.265
Guys, please don't leave me
behind! I have a plan.

37:44.283 --> 37:47.102
Your friends are safe,
but you're stuck here.

37:47.136 --> 37:48.570
What were
you thinking?

37:48.604 --> 37:50.338
Actually, I was thinking fast.

37:50.373 --> 37:51.807
Listen, there's-there's a button
on the control panel.

37:51.841 --> 37:53.325
Hit that button.

37:53.376 --> 37:55.477
I just hope
they got my message.

38:09.025 --> 38:11.026
Morgan, disconnect us from
the building's electrical line.

38:11.060 --> 38:13.128
Casey, get the van moving.

38:13.162 --> 38:15.129
Sarah, there's
a rather large window

38:15.148 --> 38:16.565
on the east side
of the building.

38:16.599 --> 38:18.433
It's the only way out...

38:18.468 --> 38:20.168
so I'm going
to be jumping through it.

38:20.203 --> 38:22.637
Casey, east side of the
building-- go, go, go, go!

38:42.875 --> 38:47.045
<i>And Sarah,</i>
<i>no matter what happens,</i>

38:47.096 --> 38:49.598
I love you.

39:01.527 --> 39:04.079
Ow! Ooh!

39:04.113 --> 39:06.531
<i>Also, if at all possible,</i>
<i>if you could check</i>

39:06.566 --> 39:08.517
to make sure
I'm still alive on the roof

39:08.551 --> 39:10.051
of the van, that would be great.

39:11.904 --> 39:12.921
Good work, Chuck!

39:12.955 --> 39:14.089
Thanks, honey.

39:14.123 --> 39:16.241
Hey, dude, that
was awesome!

39:23.499 --> 39:26.301
Listen, guys, team,
let's-let's...

39:26.335 --> 39:28.086
let's not get down, okay?

39:28.137 --> 39:30.472
Yes, that was not a classically
successful mission,

39:30.506 --> 39:32.841
but, you know,
we all made it out alive,

39:32.875 --> 39:34.543
uh, so-so, that-that's a plus.

39:34.577 --> 39:37.379
And the news says
that Bale was arrested, so,

39:37.413 --> 39:40.248
I think we should put that
in the win category.

39:40.283 --> 39:42.250
Win, uh, win
with an asterisk maybe.

39:43.486 --> 39:44.986
It's not that, Chuck.

39:45.021 --> 39:47.722
Well, okay, what is it then?

39:49.742 --> 39:51.893
Decker froze
Bale's accounts,

39:51.928 --> 39:54.329
which included the money
we transferred in.

39:54.363 --> 39:57.465
Castle and the Buy More are the
only things that aren't frozen.

39:57.500 --> 39:59.467
Decker froze

39:59.502 --> 40:00.785
all of our money

40:00.836 --> 40:02.787
because he tracked
our deposit back to us.

40:02.838 --> 40:04.806
Wait.

40:04.840 --> 40:06.841
Wait. What?

40:06.876 --> 40:09.277
All of our... all of our money?

40:09.312 --> 40:10.478
We have nothing?

40:10.513 --> 40:11.580
Payback's a bitch.

40:11.614 --> 40:13.682
Okay, think about it.

40:13.716 --> 40:15.850
We still have the Buy More,
and-and we still have me.

40:15.885 --> 40:18.753
And, uh, Sarah
and Casey, you.

40:18.788 --> 40:20.355
This is still a team.
We can still do this.

40:20.389 --> 40:22.090
I think I, uh...
I think I need a little air.

40:25.127 --> 40:26.978
Chuck...

40:27.029 --> 40:29.147
Chuck...

40:29.198 --> 40:32.601
Listen, it's okay.
We'll bounce back. We always do.

40:32.635 --> 40:35.704
Yeah.

40:35.738 --> 40:38.406
I got to... uh...

40:38.441 --> 40:40.441
I'll be back.

40:48.918 --> 40:50.919
Chuck, you found it.

40:54.090 --> 40:56.124
What's the matter?

40:57.143 --> 40:59.010
I can't afford it.

40:59.061 --> 41:01.029
If I bought it yesterday
with our fortune,

41:01.063 --> 41:02.364
we'd own it,
but now...

41:04.433 --> 41:06.301
I'm so sorry, Sarah.

41:10.640 --> 41:11.906
Well, so what?

41:11.941 --> 41:13.641
I mean, we knew
this wasn't

41:13.659 --> 41:15.310
gonna be easy,
and we didn't get married

41:15.344 --> 41:16.544
because we thought
life was easy.

41:16.579 --> 41:18.179
We got married

41:18.214 --> 41:20.649
so that we could be
there for each other

41:20.683 --> 41:22.350
when things got tough.

41:22.385 --> 41:26.154
So we could work through things
together, rich or poor.

41:26.188 --> 41:28.590
But how are we going to do this?
I mean, we got to start over.

41:28.624 --> 41:30.725
It's okay. We'll get new
clients and new missions.

41:30.760 --> 41:31.960
And we haven't
lost everything.

41:31.994 --> 41:33.678
We still have Castle
and the store.

41:33.713 --> 41:36.865
The Buy More.

41:36.899 --> 41:38.099
The Buy More.

41:38.134 --> 41:40.101
The Buy More.

41:40.136 --> 41:43.004
We use the store

41:43.039 --> 41:44.472
to support the spy team.

41:44.507 --> 41:45.807
We take Buy Mores' profits,

41:45.841 --> 41:47.609
put them
into Carmichael Industries

41:47.643 --> 41:49.444
until both companies
can make money.

41:49.478 --> 41:50.729
But in order for that to work,

41:50.780 --> 41:52.280
the store actually has
to turn a profit.

41:52.314 --> 41:53.748
We can do that.

41:53.783 --> 41:55.183
We can do that.

41:56.419 --> 41:59.120
What about me, though?

41:59.155 --> 42:00.989
You and Casey are super spies.

42:01.023 --> 42:02.323
Morgan's the Intersect.

42:02.358 --> 42:03.958
Who am I? What's my job?

42:03.993 --> 42:07.361
Chuck, you're our leader.

42:17.740 --> 42:19.591
That's the plan.

42:20.576 --> 42:22.477
As you can see,

42:22.511 --> 42:25.947
our superiors' interference
in Chuck Bartowski's life

42:25.981 --> 42:27.482
has only just begun.

42:29.351 --> 42:32.187
Now you understand
how important he is.

42:32.221 --> 42:34.756
And why he must fail.

42:34.790 --> 42:37.058
You all have your orders.

42:37.093 --> 42:39.160
This is the plan.

42:39.195 --> 42:41.830
Its final chapter.

42:43.492 --> 42:45.193
Nothing can stop it.

